3D-MC User Manual

Surface files => Planar, Road, Tin.
We mainly deal in Tin (TN3)

Linework from a project file TP3 so P indicates 'Project'

A file is it's own layer

  1. Create a New Project
    1. Power => File => Projects
    2. New
    3. Name the project
    NB: If a project is loaded control and data can be transferred over.

  2. Import 'layer' Data i.e. .ln3

    1. Power => File => Layers
    2. Import
    3. Choose file type and location from the 'What' and 'Where'
    4. Select the target file; NB: If not importing from a TP3, the target file will be imported into the current project.
    5. Ok to return

  3. Import Surface Data

    1. Power => File => Surfaces
    2. Import
    3. Select '3D Surface file (TN3, RD3, PL3)'
    4. Select the TN3 - the 'what'.
    5. Select the Drive - the 'where'.
    6. Select the file to import => OK
    7. Double-tap on the file in the Project files list.
    8. Select the target => Next. The summary screen will appear
    9. 'Finish'
    10. 'OK'
